Describe a time when you took a risk, you knew something bad might happen, but it had a positive result.
- what it was
- when and where it happened
- what might happen if you took it
- explain how it turned out in the end

I’d like to talk about a time when I took a risk by confessing my feelings to my crush, which turned out to be one of the best decisions I’ve ever made. This happened about a year ago when I was studying at an English center.

I met a girl named Hoa there, who was two years younger than me. We had known each other for quite some time, and I had developed strong feelings for her, but I didn’t have the courage to express them. We often studied together, chatted, and occasionally went out for coffee, so we had built a close connection.

However, one day she mentioned that another guy was interested in her. At that moment, I realized that I might lose my chance if I didn’t act. Even though I knew that confessing my feelings could potentially ruin our friendship, I decided to take the risk and ask her to be my girlfriend. I told myself that even if things didn’t work out, at least I wouldn’t regret staying silent.

After I confessed, she seemed a bit surprised and said she needed some time to think. Honestly, that was one of the most stressful days I’ve ever experienced. I kept checking my phone, waiting for her response.

Fortunately, later that evening, she sent me a message saying that she felt the same way. I was absolutely over the moon and couldn’t sleep that night because I was so happy.

Since then, we’ve been in a relationship for over a year, and things have been going really well. Looking back, I feel incredibly glad that I took that risk, because if I hadn’t, I might have missed out on something truly meaningful.
